    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Wash your <strong>leek[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have started to soften, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and your <strong>dried oregano </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further</p><p>Add a splash of your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>single</strong> <strong>oat </strong>to a bowl and reserve for later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has started to soften, add your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a fan of mustard? Just add a little!), <strong>remaining creamy</strong> <strong>single</strong> <strong>oat </strong>(save the rest to glaze the pastry!) and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Add a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until everything is combined \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>leek & mushroom pie filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>leek & mushroom pie filling</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!)</p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and score a criss-cross pattern across the top with a knife</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Lay the <strong>puff pastry</strong> sheet[s] over the pie dish[es] and trim off any excess</p><p>Tip: Use any excess pastry to add decorations to the pie!</p><p>Press the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish[es], then brush the <strong>reserved creamy</strong> <strong>single</strong> <strong>oat </strong>all over</p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven for 20-25 min or until puffed up, golden and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based creamy leek & mushroom pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pie is almost done, boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 1-2 min or until bright green and tender</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>peas </strong>and return them to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-creamy-leek-and-mushroom-pie/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based creamy leek & mushroom pie </strong>with the<strong> peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
